The phrase '''vale of tears''' refers to Earth and the sorrows left through life. "Vale" is a [[Middle English]] word meaning a [[valley]] or a [[dale]]. Like [[Psalm 23]]'s reference to the valley of the shadow of death, the phrase implies that the wickedness of the world makes it dark and reprieve comes only from [[God]]'s salvation.
